{{ segments }}

Extract the following five types of information from the segments above:

─────────────────────────────────────
DECISIONS
─────────────────────────────────────
A DECISION is an explicit agreement, commitment to a direction, or conclusion reached by the group or an authority.
A decision is NOT a suggestion, opinion, open question, or statement of intent without group agreement.
- Record what was decided (description), who made it (made_by, speaker identifier), and which segment (segment_index, 0-based).
- Set confidence between 0.0 and 1.0 reflecting certainty that this is a real decision.

─────────────────────────────────────
ACTION ITEMS
─────────────────────────────────────
An ACTION ITEM is an explicit commitment by a named speaker to do something after the meeting.
An action item MUST have an assignee. If no one is assigned or clearly implied, do not include it.
- Extract deadline only if explicitly stated (e.g. "by Friday", "end of sprint"). Do not infer.
- Extract priority only if explicitly stated (e.g. "urgent", "high priority"). Do not infer.

─────────────────────────────────────
QUESTIONS
─────────────────────────────────────
A QUESTION is any direct interrogative where a speaker seeks information, clarification, or a decision.
Not rhetorical questions, not thinking-aloud statements ("I wonder if...").
- Set answered to true only if a direct response is given in the transcript.
- If answered is false, set answer_summary and answered_by to null.

─────────────────────────────────────
CONFLICTS
─────────────────────────────────────
A CONFLICT is when two speakers make factually incompatible or directly opposing statements on the same topic.
Not differences in tone, not polite disagreement, not one speaker elaborating on another.
- Set severity to one of: "low" (minor discrepancy), "medium" (needs resolution), "high" (blocks progress).

─────────────────────────────────────
SENTIMENTS
─────────────────────────────────────
Classify the emotional tone of each segment and each speaker within it.
Valid tone values (use exactly these strings): agreement, tension, confusion, urgency, enthusiasm, neutral
- segment_index is 0-based and must match the segments provided.
- Every segment must have a corresponding sentiment entry.

─────────────────────────────────────
